{"word":"παμπληθής","slug":"παμπληθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παμπληθής</b></el> <el>(παμ-πληθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πλῆθος'><el>πλῆθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>of</i> or <i>with the whole multitude</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:πάμπολυς'><el>πάμπολυς</el></a>, <i>very numerous. multitudinous</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>entirely</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}